    "summary": "Re-confirmed approval with direct answers to all 4 questions",
    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED\n\nAlready sent a detailed review — check my previous message. But to directly answer your four questions:\n\n1. **AC coverage**: All six criteria met. Reviewed in detail in my prior message.\n2. **Scope split**: Correct. Step 10 = list CRUD + activate. Step 11 = clarify path (inbox -> someday/maybe). Same pattern as Steps 8/9.\n3. **Activate to inbox only**: Sufficient for V1. Inbox-only is the GTD-correct path. Bypassing clarify would let items skip the decision workflow. If users find the round-trip annoying, we add the shortcut later.\n4. **Edit capability**: Appropriate. Every list type should allow editing titles. Users make typos and refine ideas. Not mentioning it in the AC doesn't mean it shouldn't exist — it's table stakes for any list.\n\nNo blocking feedback."
  }
}
